## In the world of software, most everything takes longer to implement than you expect. And so it's not uncommon to accomplish less in a fixed amount of time than you hope.

### In a sentence (or list of features), define a GOOD outcome for your final project. I.e., what WILL you accomplish no matter what?

A good outcome will be a maze with you 6 inputs to reach the end of the maze. We are shooting for 10-20 inputs to reach the end of the maze. For the good outcome, there will be a victory message.

### In a sentence (or list of features), define a BETTER outcome for your final project. I.e., what do you THINK you can accomplish before the final project's deadline?

A better outcome will be the ability to accomplish our initial goal of 10-20 inputs. There could be a timer counting down, an enemy that appears if you go the wrong way and possibly some background music.

### In a sentence (or list of features), define a BEST outcome for your final project. I.e., what do you HOPE to accomplish before the final project's deadline?

The best outcome will be accomplishing our initial goal and adding a zombie to the program to chase the user. Including a zombie will be the best outcome for the project. Or, for the best outcome the path of the maze could be randomized so itâ€™s different every time.


